text.__SUMMARY__: Eucalyptus viridis, the green mallee, is a small native tree of Australia. It naturally occurs in Queensland, New South Wales, Victoria and South Australia.
text.Uses: Its leaves are harvested for cineole based eucalyptus oil. In New South Wales, E. viridis is important for honey production.
